ChatGPT said:

Samajh gaya ðŸ‘
Tum kehna chahte ho ki ek folder ke andar ek aur folder hai aur uske andar app.js file rakhi hai.

Chalo maan lein structure aisa hai:

chapter7-npn and tools
   â””â”€â”€ myproject
        â””â”€â”€ app.js

Is case me run karne ke 2 tarike hain:
ðŸ”¹ Tarika 1: cd se andar jao
cd "chapter7-npn and tools\myproject"
node app.js

ðŸ”¹ Tarika 2: Parent folder se hi run karo
cd "chapter7-npn and tools"
node myproject/app.js


ðŸ‘‰ Rule:

Agar tum file ke folder ke andar ho, to sirf node app.js likhna hai.

Agar tum parent folder me ho, to us folder ka path likhna hai jisme file hai, jaise node foldername/app.js.

âš¡ Shortcut tip (VS Code me):

Explorer (left side) me app.js file par right click karo

Select karo â€œOpen in Integrated Terminalâ€

Terminal automatically us file ke folder me open ho jayega âœ…

Ab sirf likho:

node app.js












